cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.SI, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the mapping of IP addresses to geographic locations, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and security (cs.CR). It also involves the use of databases and tools (cs.DB) for this purpose. The algorithm used in the study involves grouping IP addresses based on structure and delay, which is related to data mining and machine learning (cs.SI). Finally, the discussion of accuracy and encountered anomalies touches upon issues of privacy and ethics (cs.CY).
